    ]
  },
  "inBrief": {
    "text": "<strong>TechBrot</strong> delivers <strong>Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor e-commerce accounting for New York Shopify, Amazon &amp; multi-channel sellers</strong> &mdash; multi-state sales-tax nexus tracking, inventory &amp; COGS, and marketplace reconciliation, set up in your own QuickBooks file by a named ProAdvisor. The full New York e-commerce summary is below.",
    "source": "Reviewed by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at TechBrot Inc., an independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc. New York e-commerce facts (post-Wayfair economic nexus; New York&rsquo;s $500,000 AND 100-transaction threshold; marketplace-facilitator collection; FBA inventory nexus; destination-based NY/NYC 8.875% rate) verified against NY Department of Taxation and Finance guidance and the 2018 South Dakota v. Wayfair decision."
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "New York sellers start here",
    "heading": "See your real margin &mdash; and your real tax exposure.",
    "lede": "Book a free discovery call. We&rsquo;ll review your QuickBooks file and sales channels, show you where margin and nexus exposure are hiding, map the states you ship into, and send a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days. No pitch. Independent firm &mdash; does not file NY taxes or determine nexus; coordinates with your CPA.",
